You aren't allowed to access the site except through a referral link. If you want to break the rules, you can give yourself a cookie with has_referral=1.

Without an approved account, you can only view thoughts other people have posted. Or source code.

User 'elephant' has password 'sbmlv657w6ffc9gv' but because of the password being interpreted as a float (because PHP), countless other passwords also work, such as 'rtvt3dj12u' or '1dxrw487z0'. These can be generated pretty easily with an unoptimised python script brute-forcing and regex-checking hashes.

Verified users can upload images to personalise the background of their page. The system checks whether they upload a valid image. The system does not check whether the file can also be interpreted as PHP.